\i0  live? How do they get the energy they need for survival?\
Extremophiles are organisms (generally microbes) that live in extreme conditions and gain their energy through chemosynthesis. The book describes organisms that live in the deep ocean near thermal vents, and they are able to oxidize hydrogen sulfide. (Cunningham, 37)\
6. Ecosystems require energy to function. From where does most of this energy come? Where does it go?\
Most of earth's ecosystems energy comes from the Sun. Only a tiny amount of the energy received from the sun is used - most is filtered out or reflected back into space. The rest is used by to perform work (such as photosynthesis) or by organisms for heat or energy. \
7. How do green plants capture energy, and what do they do with it?\
Green plants capture energy using chlorophyll. This molecule absorbs light and uses that light energy to create chemical bonds. The process of chlorophyll and the other molecules converting water, Carbon Dioxide and energy into sugar and Oxygen is called photosynthesis.\
